------------Smart inahler project with IOT and AI for Asthma monitoring---------------

---Objective---
This project is a smart inhaler system designed to monitor environmental conditions and patient 
inhaler usage in real time. It integrates IoT sensors, cloud dashboards, and machine learning to
provide caregivers and doctors with actionable insights into asthma management

---Features---
Gas Detection (PPM):  
Uses the MQ1 sensor to measure harmful gases in the environment.
Temperature & Humidity Monitoring:  
Captures ambient conditions to assess environmental triggers.
Real-time Data Transmission:  
Sensor data is sent to Adafruit IO Dashboard and mirrored to a web application.
Threshold Alerts:  
Caretakers are notified instantly when sensor values exceed safe thresholds.
Inhaler Usage Tracking:  
Logs the exact time of inhaler use, enabling doctors to analyze usage patterns.
Abnormal Event Detection:  
Displays unusual inhaler activity or environmental exposure events with timestamps.
Live Graphs:  
Interactive visualization of gas PPM, temperature, and humidity in the web app.
AI Risk Prediction:  
A Random Forest model predicts the likelihood of future asthma attacks based on sensor data.

---Healthcare Impact---
Helps caretakers monitor patient safety remotely.
Provides doctors with detailed inhaler usage analytics.
Predicts risk of asthma attacks, enabling proactive treatment.

---Tech Stack---
Hardware: ESP32, MQ1 Gas Sensor, DHT11 (Temperature & Humidity)
IoT Platform: Adafruit IO
Web Application: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (with live data visualization)
Machine Learning: Juputer notebook
Alerts & Notifications: Threshold-based detection integrated into the app

---Workflow---
Sensors collect gas PPM, temperature, and humidity.
Data is transmitted to Adafruit IO.
Web app fetches and displays live graphs.
Threshold breaches trigger alerts for caretakers.
Inhaler usage logs are stored and analyzed.
AI model predicts risk of asthma attacks using historical data.

---.Future Improvements---
Integration with mobile apps for patient-side monitoring.
Expansion to wearable devices for continuous health tracking.
Enhanced AI models with deep learning for higher accuracy.

